  "title": "Workplace Safety Health Officer",
  "description": "<p>RESPONSIBILITIES:</p><p>To be able to effectively assess risk impact of project activities and issue Safety Stand Down when deemed necessary.</p><p>Dealing with authorities, staffs, client’s representatives, public, neighbours and other interested parties on matters related to safety & health.</p><p>Conduct daily safety inspections and compile all relevant reports and records.</p><p>Conduct regular inspection and see to it that person responsible for the NC recorded or raised by interested parties are informed to perform corrective actions with photos evidence of closure.</p><p>Conduct accident / incident investigations and recommendations on corrective actions to prevent recurrence.</p><p>Monitor and evaluate effectiveness of all corrective actions taken</p><p>Ensure reporting of incident comply with legal requirement.</p><p>Perform other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the Project Manager.</p><p></p><p>REQUIREMENTS:</p><p>Minimum 5 years of experience as Workplace Safety & Health Officer (WSHO).</p><p>Registered Workplace Safety & Health Officer (WSHO) with the Ministry of Manpower (MOM), Singapore.</p><p>Candidates with prior experience in HDB Home Improvement Programme (HIP) projects will be preferred.</p><p></p>",
